    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-03T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-03T04:00:00-05:00" n="307"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d307">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/8733: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-03T12:00:00+03:00"
                            >March 3, 1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 1:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>418. <hi rend="italic">Pravda</hi> this morning publishes the first report which
                    has appeared in the Soviet press of the entrance of German troops into Bulgaria.
                    The announcement is not prominently headlined, is very brief, and there is no
                    Soviet comment. It takes the form of a Tass item from Berlin dated March 2 as
                    follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The DNB<note n="56" xml:id="d307fn56">Deutsches Nachrichten Büro.</note>
                            reports from Sofia that German troops have entered the territory of
                            Bulgaria with the consent of the Bulgarian Government.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
